README for shadow


IMPORTANT NOTES

libxcrypt is intentionally NOT a build dependency here, even though it
appears in shadow's upstream configure checks and in some reference
Pkgfiles. glibc 2.22 still ships its own crypt() (verified via configure's
"checking for crypt in -lcrypt... yes" against glibc's libcrypt.so.1), and
this Pkgfile doesn't pass --with-bcrypt/--with-yescrypt, so shadow never
calls into libxcrypt's extended API (crypt_gensalt, crypt_r, etc.). Adding
libxcrypt here would only introduce an unnecessary libcrypt.so.1/.so.2
SONAME collision with glibc for no functional gain.

If bcrypt/yescrypt support is ever needed, this needs revisiting: add
libxcrypt as a real dependency, pass --with-bcrypt/--with-yescrypt to
configure, build libxcrypt with --disable-static and drop its unversioned
libcrypt.so post-install so both libraries can coexist (glibc keeps serving
libcrypt.so.1 for existing binaries, libxcrypt provides libcrypt.so.2 for
anything that links against it explicitly). Also update ENCRYPT_METHOD in
/etc/login.defs accordingly — it must stay SHA512 (or SHA256) as long as
libxcrypt isn't in the picture, since glibc's crypt() can't produce
yescrypt/bcrypt hashes.
